			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Zel Remus wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I thought Red Mages were just like a mix of BLM/WHM but couldn't use all their attacks.  Can RDM use stuff like Fire?  Like...damaging attacks?  Or do they only use status-type attacks?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />

<br />
Redmages can cast most of the spells of both WHM and BLM, can cast the Cure line of spells, Protect, etc.. as well as all of the Enfeebles that a WHM can use.  They can also cast the basic Water, Fire, etc.. as well as the Enfeebles that a BLM can use.  So basically you have some of each, and all of the Enfeebles. 
<br />

<br />
Furthermore, your skills will start to slack off from things like Healing and Elemental magic and you'll quickly fall behind the pure WHM &amp; BLK in those departments (seems to me you max out at between 80-90% the effectiveness of pure casters, which isn't too bad at lower levels... but I imagine the gap widens later on).  Your Enfeeble skill, however, quickly surpasses that of both the other casters.  This means that you have a greater chance of landing that Silence spell on an IT than your pure-caster cohorts.  You also get RDM-only spells, which are merely fun at first (enthunder for example) and absolutley necessary later (Refresh).  
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Zel Remus wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I also wanted to do the Dragoon/RDM at Level 30....but you made it sound like not such a great idea <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" />  ...I want the magic, but I want the melee too...what do you reccomend I should start with and use for my subs later on? </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />

<br />
The problem with RDM is it's a lousy Subjob.  It only adds a little to everything.  Think of it this way, with a pure-caster BLM or WHM subjob you'll barely have enough mana to cast 5 spells... and RDM gets only a fraction of <span style="font-style: italic">that</span>!
<br />

<br />
If you want to melee <span style="font-style: italic">and</span> cast spells, I'd recommend Pal or Drk.  Now you won't be a casting machine or anything, you'll mostly be Melee (like how Rdm are mostly casters), but you get some fun spells (and they're effective, unlike if you merely have a caster subjob).
<br />
Once you have Pal or Drk main, use maybe War or Sam for subjob (or better yet go to the Pal and Dark boards and see what they suggest).</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
